00:29:41.446 --> 00:29:42.913
Skittles?

488
00:29:42.981 --> 00:29:44.346
No. thanks.

489
00:29:44.415 --> 00:29:46.906
Listen. I got a call from Manetti.

490
00:29:46.985 --> 00:29:51.081
He tells me that your Sunshine Square
proposal is totally fucked.

491
00:29:51.156 --> 00:29:52.680
What's wrong with it?

492
00:29:52.757 --> 00:29:56.215
Well. for one thing. it violates
the zoning restrictions set forth

493
00:29:56.294 --> 00:29:59.923
in the National Historical
Preservation Act of 1966.

494
00:29:59.998 --> 00:30:02.728
Most notably. clause four.

495
00:30:02.801 --> 00:30:04.063
Shall I continue?

496
00:30:04.135 --> 00:30:06.660
- Actually. I'm familiar with that item...
- Honey.

497
00:30:06.738 --> 00:30:08.729
- Hi. Dad. am I interrupting?
- No. come in.

498
00:30:10.308 --> 00:30:13.505
I don't think you've met my daughter.
Darcie. this is Mitch Martin.

499
00:30:15.680 --> 00:30:17.614
Nice to meet you. Mitch.

500
00:30:17.682 --> 00:30:19.707
Hi. Nice to meet you.

501
00:30:19.784 --> 00:30:22.116
- How was the slumber party?
- Great. You know.

502
00:30:22.187 --> 00:30:24.348
movies and popcorn.

503
00:30:24.489 --> 00:30:26.354
She's an angel.

504
00:30:27.292 --> 00:30:30.659
It makes me sound an old man. but I can't
believe how fast she's growing up.

505
00:30:30.728 --> 00:30:33.526
- Dad. stop.
- I'm sorry honey. but it's true.

506
00:30:33.598 --> 00:30:38.092
To think that in just seven months
you'll be graduating from high school!

507
00:30:40.939 --> 00:30:42.770
You okay?

508
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:44.775
I thought you said high school.

509
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.834
Yeah. Shocking. isn't it?

510
00:30:48.012 --> 00:30:49.707
Yes. it is.

511
00:30:58.990 --> 00:31:00.287
Give me a break.

512
00:31:00.358 --> 00:31:01.950
Hey. Mitch.

513
00:31:05.897 --> 00:31:09.060
Hey. man. Did you have a good day?

514
00:31:09.133 --> 00:31:10.964
Not too bad.

515
00:31:12.170 --> 00:31:13.603
What's going on?

516
00:31:13.671 --> 00:31:17.869
I thought maybe I could crash here
tonight. if that's all right.

517
00:31:17.942 --> 00:31:20.843
Marissa is going through
some personal stuff.

518
00:31:22.380 --> 00:31:26.783
Personal stuff like you running through
the neighborhood drunk and naked?

519
00:31:26.851 --> 00:31:30.412
That and some other stuff.

520
00:31:31.956 --> 00:31:33.890
No problem.
Make yourself at home.

521
00:31:33.958 --> 00:31:35.186
Thanks.

522
00:31:35.860 --> 00:31:36.395
Gentlemen. we're discussing
a brand-new way to look at a fraternity.

523
00:31:36.395 --> 00:31:39.626
Gentlemen. we're discussing
a brand-new way to look at a fraternity.

524
00:31:39.698 --> 00:31:45.227
In other words. forget all the normal rules
that apply to both college and society.

525
00:31:45.303 --> 00:31:48.067
because this is a very big idea.
my friends.

526
00:31:48.140 --> 00:31:52.304
We are talking about a non-exclusive.
egalitarian brotherhood

527
00:31:52.377 --> 00:31:55.346
where community status
and more importantly. age.

528
00:31:55.414 --> 00:31:57.644
have no bearing whatsoever.

529
00:31:58.717 --> 00:32:00.912
Yeah? From the guy who probably
won't get in.

530
00:32:00.986 --> 00:32:03.682
- I go to school here.
- Okay.

531
00:32:03.755 --> 00:32:07.714
I was curious. what association
will you have with the actual university?

532
00:32:07.793 --> 00:32:09.920
- Who are these people?
- I don't know.

533
00:32:09.995 --> 00:32:13.328
Legally speaking.
there will be a loose affiliation.

534
00:32:13.398 --> 00:32:16.765
but we will give nothing back
to the academic community.

535
00:32:16.835 --> 00:32:20.794
As well as provide no public service
of any kind. This much I promise.

536
00:32:20.872 --> 00:32:23.102
What the hell is going on here?

537
00:32:23.175 --> 00:32:25.666
Guys. this is a very special occasion.

538
00:32:25.744 --> 00:32:29.703
The Godfather himself has been kind
enough to grace us with his presence.

539
00:32:29.781 --> 00:32:31.112
The Godfather!

540
00:32:31.183 --> 00:32:34.516
This is his damn house.
He lives here. he sleeps 20 feet away.

541
00:32:36.822 --> 00:32:38.790
We need to talk.

542
00:32:39.057 --> 00:32:40.046
Kitchen.

543
00:32:41.126 --> 00:32:44.459
Sit good for me. I'm gonna talk
to Uncle Mitch for a second.

544
00:32:44.729 --> 00:32:46.321
There you go. buddy.

545
00:32:46.398 --> 00:32:49.595
- How long have these people been here?
- All day.

546
00:32:49.668 --> 00:32:52.262
That party we had last night
has given us all kinds of street cred.

547
00:32:52.337 --> 00:32:54.100
What are you talking about?

548
00:32:54.172 --> 00:32:57.608
This is called "rush."
We're officially starting a fraternity.

549
00:32:57.676 --> 00:32:59.667
I like it. It's genius!

550
00:32:59.744 --> 00:33:01.371
You've got to be kidding me.

551
00:33:01.446 --> 00:33:03.539
You heard Pritchard. all right?
We're obligated to do this.

552
00:33:03.615 --> 00:33:07.711
This house. he says. is zoned specifically
for social services and student housing.

553
00:33:07.786 --> 00:33:09.617
Fraternity solves both of those.

554
00:33:09.688 --> 00:33:12.384
But this is my house.
I live here. Beanie.

555
00:33:12.457 --> 00:33:15.790
I'm 30 years old.
None of us are enrolled in the college.

556
00:33:15.861 --> 00:33:19.524
I understand that. You're focused
on all the wrong sort of details.

557
00:33:19.598 --> 00:33:22.567
Did you or did you not
have a good time at the party?

558
00:33:22.634 --> 00:33:24.431
I had an awesome time.

559
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:26.895
I know you had an awesome time.

560
00:33:26.972 --> 00:33:29.440
The entire town knows
you had an awesome time.

561
00:33:29.508 --> 00:33:32.068
I'm trying to ask Mitch whether
he had an awesome time.

562
00:33:32.143 --> 00:33:33.838
- I had a good time.
- Okay. that's good.

563
00:33:33.912 --> 00:33:35.937
Wouldn't you want those good times
to keep going?

564
00:33:36.014 --> 00:33:38.346
- More good...
- God. I mean...

565
00:33:38.416 --> 00:33:42.182
I don't understand. I don't know why it's
so hard for you to admit you want this.

566
00:33:42.254 --> 00:33:45.621
We got 40 guys that want this.
There must be a reason for it.

567
00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:47.954
Look. I appreciate your enthusiasm.

568
00:33:48.026 --> 00:33:51.928
I know you guys are trying to help.
but the truth of the matter is.

569
00:33:51.997 --> 00:33:55.831
I've had a hell of a day.
an even worse month.

570
00:33:55.901 --> 00:33:59.962
And the fact is.
I've got 40 strangers out in my living room

571
00:34:00.038 --> 00:34:02.768
and all I want to do is
get some fuckin' sleep.

572
00:34:02.841 --> 00:34:07.107
So. I'm sorry. but we're not
starting a fraternity.

573
00:34:07.178 --> 00:34:10.375
I don't know why you got to do it
in front of the kid. with the "F'ing."

574
00:34:10.448 --> 00:34:12.541
All you got to do is
say "earmuffs" to him.

575
00:34:12.617 --> 00:34:14.642
Then you can say.
"fuck. shit. bitch." whatever you want.

576
00:34:14.719 --> 00:34:16.050
Cock. Balls.

577
00:34:16.121 --> 00:34:18.919
I'm just proving a point.
You don't have to celebrate it. Frank.

578
00:34:18.990 --> 00:34:21.390
- Sorry.
- Don't say sorry to me.

579
00:34:21.459 --> 00:34:24.087
You let down Frank. you let down me.
you let down Max. most importantly.

580
00:34:24.162 --> 00:34:26.357
And right about now.
I'm having a real hard time

581
00:34:26.431 --> 00:34:29.992
trying to figure out why I take my time out of
my schedule to try to help you get over...

582
00:34:30.068 --> 00:34:32.093
Earmuffs. That whore that you dated.

583
00:34:32.170 --> 00:34:37.005
Wanna go out and see the other guys?
Uncle Mitch is sorry.

584
00:34:38.677 --> 00:34:40.144
Say "yes."

585
00:34:40.211 --> 00:34:41.303
Yes.

586
00:34:48.286 --> 00:34:50.311
Here's the deal.
Listen up!

587
00:34:50.388 --> 00:34:53.255
All together. we've picked
14 pledges.

588
00:34:53.324 --> 00:34:55.258
Wait. who's this guy?

589
00:34:55.326 --> 00:34:56.759
That's Blue.

590
00:34:56.827 --> 00:34:59.193
He's an old Navy vet
who hangs around my store a lot.

591
00:34:59.263 --> 00:35:00.992
But don't worry about it.
He's legit.

592
00:35:01.065 --> 00:35:03.590
He looks like he's 100 years old.
He wants to pledge?

593
00:35:03.668 --> 00:35:07.297
Are you kidding me?
The Old Man River won't shut up about it.

594
00:35:07.371 --> 00:35:09.305
Go time!

595
00:35:24.755 --> 00:35:27.417
Don't make this any harder
on yourself!

596
00:35:40.037 --> 00:35:40.969
What's going on?

597
00:35:41.038 --> 00:35:43.529
You tell anyone about this.
I'll fuckin' kill you!

598
00:35:43.607 --> 00:35:46.542
I'm kidding. We'll have him back tonight.
Okay. sweetie?

599
00:35:46.610 --> 00:35:47.941
Let's go!

600
00:35:59.790 --> 00:36:02.122
Come on. let's go.
There we go. Blue.

601
00:36:12.336 --> 00:36:14.304
Congratulations. gentlemen.

602
00:36:14.372 --> 00:36:16.465
You should all be
very proud of yourselves.

603
00:36:16.540 --> 00:36:19.509
Each and every one of you
has been hand-picked

604
00:36:19.577 --> 00:36:23.069
to represent our inaugural
pledge class.

605
00:36:23.147 --> 00:36:25.707
Over the next 21 days.

606
00:36:25.783 --> 00:36:32.347
you're all going to experience intense
mental and physical strain.

607
00:36:32.723 --> 00:36:34.213
D-ahhh!!

608
00:36:35.059 --> 00:36:37.027
Frank. just pace yourself.

609
00:36:37.862 --> 00:36:40.990
Copy that. Just got
a little overexcited. Sorry.

610
00:36:41.065 --> 00:36:45.297
At this point
you may be asking yourself.

611
00:36:45.369 --> 00:36:50.102
"Why am I holding
this 30-pound cinderblock in my hands?"

612
00:36:51.809 --> 00:36:54.141
You might also ask yourself.

613
00:36:55.179 --> 00:37:00.515
"Why does this cinderblock
have a long piece of string

614
00:37:01.419 --> 00:37:03.080
tied to it?"

615
00:37:03.687 --> 00:37:05.951
And finally.

616
00:37:07.858 --> 00:37:11.851
"Why's the other end of this string
tied securely

617
00:37:12.430 --> 00:37:14.330
to your penis?"

618
00:37:15.566 --> 00:37:18.865
And the answer. ladies. is trust.

619
00:37:19.904 --> 00:37:23.135
This is your first test.

620
00:37:23.707 --> 00:37:25.231
Spanish!

621
00:37:25.443 --> 00:37:27.911
Do you trust we've provided you
with enough slack

622
00:37:27.978 --> 00:37:30.538
so your block will land safely
on the lawn?

623
00:37:30.614 --> 00:37:32.138
Sir. yes. sir.

624
00:37:32.216 --> 00:37:34.013
- And Blue!
- Yes. sir?

625
00:37:34.085 --> 00:37:36.417
Do you trust that I do not want
to see you die here tonight?

626
00:37:36.487 --> 00:37:38.819
- Sir. yes. sir.
- Blue. you're my boy!

627
00:37:38.889 --> 00:37:40.220
Thank you. sir.

628
00:37:42.726 --> 00:37:44.284
About face.

629
00:37:47.598 --> 00:37:49.361
Step to the edge!

630
00:37:53.304 --> 00:37:55.704
Pledges. prepare to release!

631
00:37:57.908 --> 00:37:59.500
One...

632
00:37:59.877 --> 00:38:01.139
two...

633
00:38:01.612 --> 00:38:03.842
three! Release!

634
00:38:07.685 --> 00:38:09.949
Aahh!

635
00:38:11.222 --> 00:38:12.484
Oh...!

636
00:38:14.892 --> 00:38:17.122
Wasn't meant to happen
like that. Weensie!

637
00:38:17.194 --> 00:38:19.856
Walk it off. big guy.
We're coming down.

638
00:38:20.431 --> 00:38:22.422
* <i>One. two. three. four</i>

639
00:38:22.500 --> 00:38:24.525
* <i>One. two. three. four</i>

640
00:38:24.602 --> 00:38:26.968
* <i>I've been laid more times than God</i>

641
00:38:27.037 --> 00:38:29.198
* <i>Got six kids in Laung</i>- <i>Pau</i>- <i>Lad</i>

642
00:38:29.273 --> 00:38:33.232
* <i>One two three four</i>
<i>One two three four</i>

643
00:38:33.410 --> 00:38:37.779
* <i>I don't know. but it's been said</i>
<i>One more lap and I'll be dead</i>

644
00:38:37.848 --> 00:38:39.713
- * <i>One two three four...</i>
- <i>Faster!</i>

645
00:38:41.385 --> 00:38:44.354
Jesus. Who are these people?

646
00:38:47.324 --> 00:38:49.884
Patricia. get security
to the South Lawn.

647
00:38:49.960 --> 00:38:52.656
We have an illegal off-road vehicle
operating without a permit.

648
00:38:52.730 --> 00:38:54.857
<i>They've already been called. sir.</i>

649
00:38:54.932 --> 00:38:57.196
Call them again.

650
00:39:02.072 --> 00:39:06.475
It's been two weeks.
How are these guys still a fraternity?

651
00:39:06.544 --> 00:39:08.307
They're not a fraternity. sir.

652
00:39:08.379 --> 00:39:11.314
They've been approved for temporary
status by the student council.

653
00:39:11.382 --> 00:39:13.714
Half these guys don't even
go to the school.

654
00:39:13.784 --> 00:39:15.775
You see the one guy. he's like 90.

655
00:39:15.853 --> 00:39:18.617
Technically. that doesn't matter.
They found a loophole.

656
00:39:18.689 --> 00:39:20.179
- A loophole?
- Yes.

657
00:39:20.257 --> 00:39:21.815
Well. it's interesting. sir.

658
00:39:21.892 --> 00:39:25.259
As stupid as they appear.
they're actually very good at paperwork.

659
00:39:25.329 --> 00:39:27.058
It's quite an anomaly.

660
00:39:27.665 --> 00:39:30.429
I'm sorry. is that funny?
Are you a standup comic?

661
00:39:30.501 --> 00:39:31.991
Is that what you do now?

662
00:39:34.972 --> 00:39:37.133
This is me leaving. This is me leaving.

663
00:39:48.919 --> 00:39:50.614
There he is.

664
00:39:51.488 --> 00:39:53.217
What's going on. brother?

665
00:39:53.290 --> 00:39:55.520
Nothing.
Just making some copies.

666
00:39:56.827 --> 00:39:58.317
See you later.

667
00:39:58.395 --> 00:40:00.590
Hey. Mitch. hang on a second.

668
00:40:00.664 --> 00:40:03.462
I heard you guys are
starting up a fraternity.

669
00:40:03.534 --> 00:40:04.933
Who told you that?

670
00:40:05.002 --> 00:40:07.095
Nobody. Is it true?

671
00:40:07.171 --> 00:40:09.605
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Right.

672
00:40:09.673 --> 00:40:12.141
It sounds cool. man.
I want in.

673
00:40:13.277 --> 00:40:16.576
Listen to me.
There is no fraternity.

674
00:40:16.647 --> 00:40:18.979
I don't even know
what you're talking about.

675
00:40:19.049 --> 00:40:21.745
You listen to me.
I need this. okay?

676
00:40:21.819 --> 00:40:26.017
My wife. my job. my kids.
Every day is exactly the same.

677
00:40:26.090 --> 00:40:28.422
I go golfing on Sundays.

678
00:40:28.492 --> 00:40:30.585
I hate golf.

679
00:40:30.661 --> 00:40:32.993
Don't blackball me. Mitch.
Please.

680
00:40:33.063 --> 00:40:36.658
I am not blackballing you.
We work together. Walsh.

681
00:40:36.734 --> 00:40:39.931
And I don't want to mix work
with whatever it is I do at home.

682
00:40:40.304 --> 00:40:43.364
Trust me. you're not
missing anything. anyways.

683
00:40:43.440 --> 00:40:44.600
Really?

684
00:40:44.675 --> 00:40:47.109
Heard you hooked up
with Goldberg's daughter.

685
00:40:47.478 --> 00:40:50.106
Sorry. Sorry.

686
00:40:51.148 --> 00:40:53.241
That is untrue!

687
00:40:57.187 --> 00:40:59.712
Hey. Mitch. all I'm saying is
think about it. okay?

688
00:40:59.790 --> 00:41:01.392
Think about it!

689
00:41:01.392 --> 00:41:03.519
So what?
Who cares if you work with the guy?

690
00:41:03.594 --> 00:41:06.028
I do. I mean. I have a career
to worry about.

691
00:41:06.097 --> 00:41:10.124
You're killing me. You really need
to start embracing this whole thing here.

692
00:41:10.201 --> 00:41:13.136
The frustrating thing is I don't think
you appreciate everything I did for you.

693
00:41:13.204 --> 00:41:15.195
- For me?
- Yeah. for you.

694
00:41:15.273 --> 00:41:18.504
You think I like avoiding my wife and kids
to hang out with 19-year-old girls all day?

695
00:41:18.576 --> 00:41:20.271
- Yeah. I do.
- Well. I don't. man.

696
00:41:20.344 --> 00:41:22.539
- I'm doing this whole thing for you.
- Hello.

697
00:41:22.613 --> 00:41:25.844
Nicole. how's it going?
Who's this?

698
00:41:25.917 --> 00:41:28.147
This is my daughter. Amanda.
Say hi. sweetie.

699
00:41:28.219 --> 00:41:30.585
Hi. Amanda.
You remember Nicole. right?

700
00:41:30.655 --> 00:41:34.113
Yeah. we did a little chicken dancing
at the wedding. actually.

701
00:41:34.192 --> 00:41:36.353
- How you been?
- Fine. thanks.

702
00:41:36.427 --> 00:41:37.223
Good.

703
00:41:37.295 --> 00:41:40.230
I actually wanted
to apologize to you about the wedding.

704
00:41:40.298 --> 00:41:42.163
I hope I didn't embarrass you.

705
00:41:42.233 --> 00:41:45.168
It's okay.
You just embarrassed yourself.

706
00:41:45.236 --> 00:41:48.865
- I brought you a housewarming gift.
- That is really nice.

707
00:41:48.940 --> 00:41:52.706
It's just a CD holder. you know. for your
desk or whatever. I thought it was...

708
00:41:52.777 --> 00:41:55.371
No. that thing's a piece of crap.
Awful.

709
00:41:56.681 --> 00:41:59.411
- I stopped selling it six months ago.
- Please. hey. Beanie.

710
00:41:59.483 --> 00:42:01.110
- Thanks.
- A lot of complaints.

711
00:42:01.185 --> 00:42:03.483
- But it's a nice gesture. I think.
- No. this is cool.

712
00:42:03.554 --> 00:42:05.044
Hey. Godfather!

713
00:42:05.122 --> 00:42:07.522
- What's up?
- Yo. you the man. dog!

714
00:42:07.592 --> 00:42:09.025
See you around. homey!

715
00:42:09.093 --> 00:42:11.084
Did that guy just call you
the Godfather?

716
00:42:11.162 --> 00:42:13.824
Must be joking around or something.

717
00:42:13.898 --> 00:42:15.559
Where are you guys living now?

718
00:42:15.633 --> 00:42:18.727
We're staying with my dad for awhile.
until I find something better.

719
00:42:18.803 --> 00:42:20.771
The move's been a little rough on Amanda.

720
00:42:20.838 --> 00:42:25.537
My son Max is turning six on Sunday.
We're having a birthday party for him.

721
00:42:25.610 --> 00:42:27.976
Just like. petting zoo and clowns.
stuff like that.

722
00:42:28.045 --> 00:42:29.979
But you guys are welcome to come.
if you like.

723
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:32.106
- Great idea! You should definitely come.
- Okay.

724
00:42:32.183 --> 00:42:35.744
What do you guys like better?
Nurse or cheerleader?

725
00:42:37.655 --> 00:42:39.020
